///
/// Description - design window
@NODE VIEW "Design window"

@{fg highlight}@{B}@{U}Design window@{fg text}@{UB}@{UU}

@{fg highlight}@{B}Calling:@{fg text}@{UB}
  Main window:
    @{B}menu:@{UB}      View|Design...

@{fg highlight}@{B}Description:@{fg text}@{UB}
  You can edit design of main window by mouse and keyboard. You can
  change size of fields by moving pointer over one of the borders and
  drag it to their destination place. You can move fields using mouse
  by drag&drop any field to any position.


@{fg highlight}@{B}Shortcuts:@{fg text}@{UB}
  @{B}[CURSOR RIGHT]/[CURSOR LEFT]@{UB}
    moves cursor to the next/previous field

  @{B}[CURSOR UP]/[CURSOR DOWN]@{UB}
    moves cursor to the next/previous line

  @{B}[Enter]@{UB}
    depends where cursor is placed, moves field to new line or add
    space between two lines

  @{B}[TAB]@{UB}
    inserts TAB between two lines

  @{B}[<underscore character>]@{UB}
    moves cursor into that field

  @{B}[Shift] [<underscore character>]@{UB}
    @{"edits field" LINK DEFINITION}

  @{B}[Ctrl] [Shift] [<underscore character>]@{UB}
    hides/shows field

  @{B}[<doubleclick on the field>]@{UB}
    @{"edits field" LINK DEFINITION}

  @{B}[Alt] [<doubleclick on the field>]@{UB}
    @{"edits field attributes" LINK OPCJE}

  @{B}[Ctrl] [<doubleclick on the field>]@{UB}
    @{"edits field label" LINK LABELS}

  @{B}[Ctrl] [Shift] [<doubleclick on the field>]@{UB}
    hides/shows field

  @{B}[Ctrl] [Shift] [Enter]@{UB}
    shows all fields

@{fg highlight}@{B}Menu:@{fg text}@{UB}
  @{B}View@{UB}
    @{B}Restore@{UB}
      Restores default design of view.
    @{B}Load...@{UB}
      Loads view.
    @{B}Save...@{UB}
      Saves view.
    @{B}Tab size...@{UB}
      Sets tab size.
    @{B}Apply@{UB}
      Accepts all changes and returns to main window.
    @{B}Cancel@{UB}
      Discards all changes and returns to main window.

  @{B}Field@{UB}
    @{B}Cut@{UB}
      Cuts field to buffer.
    @{B}>Copy@{UB}
      Copys field to buffer.
    @{B}Paste@{UB}
      Pastes field from buffer.
    @{B}Insert...@{UB}
      Inserts new field.
    @{B}Delete@{UB}
      Removes field.
    @{B}Definition...@{UB}
      @{"Edits field definition" LINK DEFINITION}.
    @{B}Label...@{UB}
      @{"Edits field label" LINK LABELS}.
    @{B}Attributes...@{UB}
      for field of type:
        @{" String      " LINK STRINGATRR}
        @{" Amount      " LINK STRINGATRR}
        @{" Boolean     " LINK BOOLEANATRR}
        @{" Cycle       " LINK CYCLEATRR}
        @{" Button      " LINK BUTTONATRR}
        @{" Text        " LINK TEXTATRR}
    @{B}ARexx...@{UB}
      Sets @{"ARexx program" LINK PRGRX} for field.

@ENDNODE
///
/// Description - printing
@NODE PRINTING "Printing"

@{fg highlight}@{B}@{U}Printing@{fg text}@{UB}@{UU}

@{fg highlight}@{B}Calling:@{fg text}@{UB}
  Main window:
    @{B}menu:@{UB}      Project|Print...

@{fg highlight}@{B}Description:@{fg text}@{UB}
  Using this option you can print or export to file current project in
  different formats.

@{fg highlight}@{B}Gadgets:@{fg text}@{UB}
  @{B}Output to@{UB}
    Here you can specify where you want to print your project. Gadget at the
    right side is used to choose a file to which you want to print the project.

  @{B}Print@{UB}
    Which records will be printed. Gadget at the right side is used to
    specify which records will be printed (all from range, only marked
    or only unmarked).

  @{B}Format@{UB}
    Sets printout format.

  @{B}Header@{UB}
    Name of the file which will be printed before all records.

  @{B}Footer@{UB}
    Name of the file which will be printed after all records.

  @{B}Record header@{UB}
    Text which will be printed before every record. You can use @{"variables" LINK VAR}.

  @{B}Record footer@{UB}
    Text which will be printed after every record. You can use @{"variables" LINK VAR}.

  @{B}Print hidden fields@{UB}
    Prints also hidden fields.

  @{B}Print@{UB}
    Starts printing.

@ENDNODE
///
/// Description - searching
@NODE SEARCHING "Searching records"

@{fg highlight}@{B}@{U}Searching records@{fg text}@{UB}@{UU}

@{fg highlight}@{B}Calling:@{fg text}@{UB}
  Main window:
    @{B}menu:@{UB}      Search|Find...
    @{B}popupmenu:@{UB} Find...

  If you select this option from menu or by shortcut holding [Shift]
  key, find record window will be opened without last search criterion.

@{fg highlight}@{B}Description:@{fg text}@{UB}
  For all types of fields you can enter searching pattern. All
  AmigaDOS patterns are accepted (exclude amount fields) for example:
  pattern (#?ski|#?ska) will be matched to all words which ends with
  "ski" or "ska" characters. If you want to know more, please read
  AmigaDOS manual.

  For cycle and boolean fields it's not necesary to enter searched
  text, you can used "«" gadget at the right side of text gadget, and
  select value which you want to find.

  If you want to research using the same values like last entered,
  select "Search|Find next" or "Search|Find prev". Searching starts
  from current record, with only one different: in first case database
  will be searched from current to last record, in second case from
  current to first record.

@{fg highlight}@{B}Shortcuts:@{fg text}@{UB}
  @{B}[Enter]@{UB}
     Starts searching.

  @{B}[Shift] [Enter]@{UB}
    Starts searching. All matched records will be placed into @{"browsing" LINK BROWSING} window.

@{fg highlight}@{B}Gadgets:@{fg text}@{UB}
  @{B}Criterion@{UB}
    In that gadget you can saw list of all fields for which you could
    specify searching pattern. Text gadget below list is used to enter
    searching pattern. Gadget at the left side is used to select equal
    operator. Two last operators (marked as CS) are case sensitive.

  @{B}Search@{UB}
    Here you can specify searching range:
      All       - All records will be searched.
      Up        - All records from current to first.
      Down      - All records from current to last.
      ·         - Records from specified range.

  @{B}Find all@{UB}
    Starts searching. All matched records will be placed into the
    @{"browsing" LINK BROWSING} window.

@ENDNODE
///
/// Description - sorting
@NODE SORTING "Sorting records"

@{fg highlight}@{B}@{U}Sorting records@{fg text}@{UB}@{UU}

@{fg highlight}@{B}Calling:@{fg text}@{UB}
  Main window:
    @{B}menu:@{UB}      Record|Sort|By...

  If you select this option from menu or by shortcut holding [SHIFT]
  key, find record window will be opened without last sort criterion.

@{fg highlight}@{B}Gadgets:@{fg text}@{UB}
  @{B}Position@{UB}
    Using this gadget or clicking in order on the fields you could
    specify order of sorting fields of records, for example: if
    project contains fields: First name, Last name, Address and you
    specify criterion:
      First name          A-Z 2
      Last name           A-Z 1
      Address             Z-A 3
    program sorts records by the "Last name" field, but if the program
    found 2 or more records with the same "Last names", field "First
    name" decides about order, etc.

  @{B}Order@{UB}
    Uses to specify sorting order: A-Z - increasing, Z-A - decreasing.

  @{B}Remove@{UB}
    Removes selected field from sorting criterion.

@ENDNODE
///
/// Description - browsing
@NODE BROWSING "Browsing records"

@{fg highlight}@{B}@{U}Browsing records@{fg text}@{UB}@{UU}

@{fg highlight}@{B}Calling:@{fg text}@{UB}
  Main window:
    @{B}menu:@{UB}      Field|Browse...
    @{B}popupmenu:@{UB} Browse...
    @{B}shortcut:@{UB}  Doubleclick nearby the field

@{fg highlight}@{B}Description:@{fg text}@{UB}
  Using cycle gadget at the top of the window you could select field
  by which field you want to browse database.

@{fg highlight}@{B}Shortcuts:@{fg text}@{UB}
  @{B}[CURSOR UP]/[CURSOR DOWN]@{UB}
    jumps to next/previous record

  @{B}[ENTER]@{UB}
    closes window

  @{B}[<doubleclick on any position>]@{UB}
    closes window

@{fg highlight}@{B}Menu:@{fg text}@{UB}
  @{B}Browse@{UB}
    @{B}Only marked@{UB}
      Shows only marked records.
    @{B}Last found@{UB}
      Shows only that records which was founded using "All" option in
      @{"searching" LINK SEARCHING} window.
    @{B}All@{UB}
      Shows all records.
    @{B}Statistics...@{UB}
      @{"statistics of field values." LINK STATISTICS}
    @{B}Close@{UB}
      Closes window.

  @{B}Order@{UB}
    Using this option you can specify sorting order.

@{fg highlight}@{B}Gadgets:@{fg text}@{UB}
  @{B}Pattern@{UB}
    Here you can specify pattern. Only records which match the pattern
    will be displayed in the window.

@ENDNODE
///
/// Description - statistics
@NODE STATISTICS "Statistics"

@{fg highlight}@{B}@{U}Statistics@{fg text}@{UB}@{UU}

@{fg highlight}@{B}Calling:@{fg text}@{UB}
  Main window:
    @{B}menu:@{UB}      Field|Statistics...
    @{B}popupmenu:@{UB} Statistics...

@{fg highlight}@{B}Description:@{fg text}@{UB}
  Field for which statistics will be calculated is selected by cycle
  gadget, which is placed above list with results.

@{fg highlight}@{B}Gadgets:@{fg text}@{UB}
  @{B}Save...@{UB}
    Saves statistics.

  @{B}Save TSV...@{UB}
    Saves statistics as ASCII TSV.

@ENDNODE
