///
/// Settings - protection
@NODE PASSETS "Project settings - Protection"

@{fg highlight}@{B}@{U}Project settings - Protection@{fg text}@{UB}@{UU}

@{fg highlight}@{B}Calling:@{fg text}@{UB}
  Main window:
    @{B}menu:@{UB}      Project|Settings...

@{fg highlight}@{B}Description:@{fg text}@{UB}
  Protect the project with a password.

@{fg highlight}@{B}Gadgets:@{fg text}@{UB}
  @{B}Password@{UB}
    Password which will be used to protect the project.

  @{B}Verify@{UB}
    Password verification. Please type here password again.

  @{B}Only check password before saving@{UB}
    Password will not be checked when someone tries to open a file, but
    only, if someone selects the "Save" option.

@ENDNODE
///
/// Settings - arexx
@NODE ARXSETS "Project settings - ARexx"

@{fg highlight}@{B}@{U}Project settings - ARexx@{fg text}@{UB}@{UU}

@{fg highlight}@{B}Calling:@{fg text}@{UB}
  Main window:
    @{B}menu:@{UB}      Project|Settings...

@{fg highlight}@{B}Description:@{fg text}@{UB}
  Project settings to ARexx interface.

@{fg highlight}@{B}Gadgets:@{fg text}@{UB}
  @{B}Port name@{UB}
    Name for ARexx port for project. If you leave this field empty,
    project will have "XBAZE" ARexx port.

  @{B}Console@{UB}
    Console, where all returned values from program will be shown.

  @{B}Keep programs in "T:"@{UB}
    All ARexx programs for this project will be kept in logical
    volume "T:", for much faster running.

@ENDNODE
///
/// Settings - menu
@NODE MENUSETS "Project settings - Menu"

@{fg highlight}@{B}@{U}Project settings - Menu@{fg text}@{UB}@{UU}

@{fg highlight}@{B}Calling:@{fg text}@{UB}
  Main window:
    @{B}menu:@{UB}      Project|Settings...

@{fg highlight}@{B}Description:@{fg text}@{UB}
  Assigns ARexx programs and views to menu.

@{fg highlight}@{B}Gadgets:@{fg text}@{UB}
  @{B}Menu@{UB}
    Selects menu for which files will be assigned.

  @{B}Shortcut@{UB}
    Which will call given file.

  @{B}Name@{UB}
    Name which will be shown in the menu.

  @{B}File@{UB}
    Path to the file, which will be assigned.

@ENDNODE
///
/// Settings - program settings
@NODE PRGSETS "Program settings"

@{fg highlight}@{B}@{U}Program settings@{fg text}@{UB}@{UU}

@{fg highlight}@{B}Calling:@{fg text}@{UB}
  Main window:
    @{B}menu:@{UB}      Project|Settings...

@{fg highlight}@{B}Gadgets:@{fg text}@{UB}
  @{B}Pubscreen@{UB}
    Name of the public screen on which main window of XBaze will be
    opened. If program couldn't find specifed screen, main window will
    be opened on Workbench screen.

  @{B}Font@{UB}
    Font which will be used by program, syntax:
      <font name/font size>.

  @{B}Data dir@{UB}
    Directory from which files will be placed in "*" menu. This makes
    easier opening often used projects.

  @{B}Statistics precision (digits after point)@{UB}
    Precision with which all statistics will be calculated. Selected
    number specify number of digits after point.

  @{B}Create icons@{UB}
    Enables saving icons for projects project.

  @{B}Sort using locale@{UB}
    If this option is enabled, all strings will be compared through
    function in the system locale.library. If you sort databases in
    english or polish language you don't have to specify that option.

  @{B}Ignore saved window position@{UB}
    Program will ignore saved window positions.

  @{B}Progress indicator@{UB}
    Enables progress indicator.

  @{B}Start XBaze iconified@{UB}
    Program starts as iconified.

  @{B}Use screen font in requesters and child windows@{UB}
    Selected font will be used only in main window.

  @{B}Toolbar on left border@{UB}
    Toolbar will be placed on left window border. If this option will
    be disabled, toolbar will be placed on bottom window border.

  @{B}No size gadget@{UB}
    Main window won't have resizing gadget.

  @{B}No navigation buttons@{UB}
    Gadgets to navigate through recrods won't be placed at the botttom
    window border.


@ENDNODE
